cks for immediate behavior, asserting `isDispatchNeeded` for the EDT. I want to create a robust test using runBlocking with a timeout. I wonder if launching a child coroutine within `withContext(Dispatchers.Swing)` will delay its execution until the parent yields. I’ll need to design this test carefully and ensure I’m using `yield` correctly in the context of CoroutineScope.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying CoroutineScope in context**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the `withContext(context) {}` block and whether it's a suspend CoroutineScope. It seems like I’m correct! If I launch a coroutine with `Dispatchers.Swing` while on the EDT, it should mark `dispatchNeeded` as true, which means it queues the child coroutine. The child can’t run until the EDT is available again or suspends its execution. This highlights how important the dispatching behavior is for proper coroutine execution in a Swing environment.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Swing dispatcher behavior**\\n\\nI’m analyzing the Swing regular on EDT. It’s true that a job won’t complete immediately after launch; I need to ensure that `job.isCompleted` is false since the outer coroutine must finish first. There's also the potential issue with child jobs running immediately if the current EDT is busy. I’m considering `Dispatchers.Main.immediate` behavior and how it might relate to Swing.immediate, which seems to have some duplication issues. I'll check if the `Swing` dispatcher is deprecated or internal.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test coverage**\\n\\nI need to gather sources to ensure I'm not risking deprecated components. If something is deprecated, I expect there would be compiler warnings, which I should pay attention to. I’m also thinking about testing exception handling on the Swing dispatcher to see how coroutines handle uncaught exceptions. This isn't library-specific, so I should analyze the current coverage in the final output. Plus, I'll only modify the test file and add one specific test, ensuring it’s an exact edit.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_88sE6TQtb2sxas3MYnyX21Kg|fc_017d25d4156171e10169faaeab777c81a28850a4070adc5cc9", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-coroutines-swing/1.10.2/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlinx/kotlinx_coroutines_swing/Kotlinx_coroutines_swingTest.kt", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    fun asyncWorkComposesOnSwingDispatcher(): Unit = runBlocking {\n        withTimeout(5_000) {\n            val combined: String = withContext(Dispatchers.Swing) {\n                val greeting = async(Dispatchers.Swing.immediate) {\n                    assertThat(SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()).isTrue()\n                    \"hello\"\n                }\n                val target = async(Dispatchers.Swing.immediate) {\n                    assertThat(SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()).isTrue()\n                    \"swing\"\n                }\n\n                \"${greeting.await()} ${target.await()}\"\n            }\n\n            assertThat(combined).isEqualTo(\"hello swing\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun delayResumesOnEventDispatchThreadAndCancellationStopsPendingContinuation(): Unit = runBlocking {", "newText": "    @Test\n    fun asyncWorkComposesOnSwingDispatcher(): Unit = runBlocking {\n        withTimeout(5_000) {\n            val combined: String = withContext(Dispatchers.Swing) {\n                val greeting = async(Dispatchers.Swing.immediate) {\n                    assertThat(SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()).isTrue()\n                    \"hello\"\n                }\n                val target = async(Dispatchers.Swing.immediate) {\n                    assertThat(SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()).isTrue()\n                    \"swing\"\n                }\n\n                \"${greeting.await()} ${target.await()}\"\n            }\n\n            assertThat(combined).isEqualTo(\"hello swing\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun swingDispatcherPostsNestedWorkInsteadOfRunningInlineOnEventDispatchThread(): Unit = runBlocking {\n        withTimeout(5_000) {\n            val events: MutableList<String> = mutableListOf()\n\n            withContext(Dispatchers.Swing) {\n                events += \"outer-start\"\n                val job = launch(Dispatchers.Swing) {\n                    assertThat(SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()).isTrue()\n                    events += \"nested\"\n                }\n\n                assertThat(job.isCompleted).isFalse()\n                events += \"outer-after-launch\"\n            }\n\n            assertThat(events).containsExactly(\"outer-start\", \"outer-after-launch\", \"nested\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun delayResumesOnEventDispatchThreadAndCancellationStopsPendingContinuation(): Unit = runBlocking {"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-coroutines-swing/1.10.2/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlinx/kotlinx_coroutines_swing/Kotlinx_coroutines_swingTest.kt\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"    @Test\\n    fun asyncWorkComposesOnSwingDispatcher(): Unit = runBlocking {\\n        withTimeout(5_000) {\\n            val combined: String = withContext(Dispatchers.Swing) {\\n                val greeting = async(Dispatchers.Swing.immediate) {\\n                    assertThat(SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()).isTrue()\\n                    \\\"hello\\\"\\n                }\\n                val target = async(Dispatchers.Swing.immediate) {\\n                    assertThat(SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()).isTrue()\\n                    \\\"swing\\\"\\n                }\\n\\n                \\\"${greeting.await()} ${target.await()}\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            assertThat(combined).isEqualTo(\\\"hello swing\\\")\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    fun delayResumesOnEventDispatchThreadAndCancellationStopsPendingContinuation(): Unit = runBlocking {\",\